@jean-christophe-manciot I have written a demo plugin please have look and let me know you inputs/comments

```Python
"""
Tree output plugin
Idea copied from libsmi.
"""

from pyang import plugin
from pyang import statements

def pyang_plugin_init():
    plugin.register_plugin(YAMLPlugin())

class YAMLPlugin(plugin.PyangPlugin):

    def add_output_format(self, fmts):
        self.multiple_modules = True
        fmts["yaml"] = self

    def setup_fmt(self, ctx):
        """Part of the Pyang plug-in interface."""
        ctx.implicit_errors = False

    def emit(self, ctx, modules, fd):
        for (epos, etag, eargs) in ctx.errors:
            if error.is_error(error.err_level(etag)):
                raise error.EmitError("YAML plugin needs a valid module")
    
        for module in modules:
            self.process_children(module)

    def process_children(self, node, indent=0):
        """
        Process all children of `node`, except "rpc" and "notification".
        """
        indentStr = ' ' * indent
        print indentStr, "- %s:%s" % (node.arg, node.keyword)
        indent = indent + 2
        for ch in node.i_children:
            if ch.keyword in ["rpc", "notification"]: continue
            if ch.keyword in ["container", "list", "choice"]:
                self.process_children(ch, indent+2)
            elif ch.keyword in ["leaf", "leaf-list"]:
                print ' ' * indent, "%s: %s" % (ch.arg, self.base_type(ch.search_one("type")))

    def base_type(self, type):
        """Return the base type of `type`."""
        while 1:
            if type.arg == "leafref":
                node = type.i_type_spec.i_target_node
            elif type.i_typedef is None:
                break
            else:
                node = type.i_typedef
            type = node.search_one("type")
        if type.arg == "decimal64":
            return [type.arg, int(type.search_one("fraction-digits").arg)]
        elif type.arg == "union":
            return [type.arg, [self.base_type(x) for x in type.i_type_spec.types]]
        else:
            return type.arg
```

Yes, I see lots of '$v-number' entries from hgetall. Since I wrote a simple python script to dump them, please feel free to let me know if you need these entries. I have started to read the source code of durable_rules recently, hoping that I could offer more help on this project. However, I have came across the following code in rete.c
```C
static unsigned int linkAlpha(ruleset *tree,
                              unsigned int parentOffset,
                              unsigned int nextOffset) {

       // some code here ...
        result = ensureNextHashset(tree, parentAlpha);
        if (result != RULES_OK) {
            return result;
        }

        unsigned int *parentNext = &tree->nextPool[parentAlpha->value.a.nextOffset];
        unsigned int hash = nextNode->value.a.hash;
        for (entry = hash & HASH_MASK; parentNext[entry] != 0; entry = (entry + 1) % NEXT_BUCKET_LENGTH) {
            if ((entry + 1) % NEXT_BUCKET_LENGTH == (hash & HASH_MASK)) {
                return ERR_RULE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED;
            }
        }

        parentNext[entry] = nextOffset;
}
```

The HASH_MASK and NEXT_BUCKET_LENGTH is defined in rules.h
```C
#define NEXT_BUCKET_LENGTH 512
#define NEXT_LIST_LENGTH 32
#define BETA_LIST_LENGTH 16
#define HASH_MASK 0x1F
```

My question is, since the HASH_MASK makes the entry always goes between 0 to 31, why do we need to allocate a bucket length up to 512 slots in nextPool for nextOffset field?

Thanks again for your effort on this issue.

