I don't know if it's my particular case, but `from_picker.datepickerdata.date()` happens to be `null`, while `bootstrap-datetimepicker.js` specifies a condition for exactly boolean `false`, and this breaks everything:
```javascript
picker.minDate = function (minDate) {
    if (arguments.length === 0) {
        return options.minDate ? options.minDate.clone() : options.minDate;
    }

    if ((typeof minDate === 'boolean') && minDate === false) {
        options.minDate = false;
        update();
        return picker;
    }
...
```

