@sgt101 @dahlem A few other tips...

- You can reduce the number of wav's used in training, dev, and testing using the command line arguments `limit_train`, `limit_dev`, and `limit_test` which take the number of training, dev, and test wav's to use respectively
- We use curriculum learning so the shortest wavs are in the initial batches the longest are in the final batches. However, batch size is dependent only on the largest wavs. So one normally has to wait until the last batch to determine if batch size is correct. However, one can temporarily sort by largest wav first by changing the sort order here[[1](https://github.com/mozilla/DeepSpeech/blob/master/util/data_set_helpers.py#L81)] then the OOM occur right away with no wait.

@andrewharvey The CLI was designed specifically to use `TILESET` as the basis for naming, based on the feedback that keeping tileset *name* and *id* consistent was a high priority for our users. 

Keeping tileset names consistent with the *original filenames* is certainly possible with some scripting. But it's not a goal of this project or a high priority for most use cases.

Because current users rely on the behavior of extracting the `name` from the `TILESET`, implement ing this change would breaking existing scripts. I'm inclined to keep the existing behavior as a result.

